On 4/22/10 9:41 PM, Jens Bengtsson wrote:
&gt; Yeah, that&#39;s what I thought. But I eliminated the TranscludedDecideRule setting and it still went and crawled from other domains as well. I&#39;ve also setup a regexp decide rule so it won&#39;t download stuff like css and a bunch of other file types, which it still does anyways it seems. So I think something is wrong with my setup.

Then it&#39;s likely some other change from the default rules is bringing 
other URIs in. You&#39;re welcome to post the excerpt of your configuration 
where your scoping rules are defined for review.

- Gordon @ IA

&gt; --- In archive-crawler@yahoogroups.com, Gordon Mohr&lt;gojomo@...&gt;  wrote:
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; See this FAQ:
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; https://webarchive.jira.com/wiki/display/Heritrix/unexpected+offsite+content
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; Heritrix is not getting everything on those other domains -- only those
&gt;&gt; things that appear necessary to render pages on the main scope. (The
&gt;&gt; crawl.log lines for the off-domain URLs will show &#39;hops path&#39; strings like
&gt;&gt; &quot;EE&quot; or &quot;RE&quot; or &quot;ERX&quot;. That means some combination of &#39;E&#39;mbeds,
&gt;&gt; &#39;R&#39;edirects, and &#39;X&#39;speculative outinks led the crawler down those paths.
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; - Gordon @ IA
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; On 4/22/10 12:59 PM, Jens Bengtsson wrote:
&gt;&gt;&gt; Then I guess H3 is broken for me.
&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt; Because if I define
&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt; www.idg.se as my seed
&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt; and then have
&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt; seedsAsSurtPrefixes=true for SurtPrefixedDecideRule
&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt; It still results in Heretrix crawling every domain it comes in contact with. My mirror folder filled up with 100+ directories with different domains that were crawled.
&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt; --- In archive-crawler@yahoogroups.com, Gordon Mohr&lt;gojomo@&gt;   wrote:
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; On 4/21/10 9:58 PM, Jens Bengtsson wrote:
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; OK, so I don&#39;t need to use OnHostsDecideRule. Is the same true for OnDomainDecideRule? Can I achieve the same &quot;lockdown&quot; with SurtPrefixedDecideRule?
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; The same is true for OnDomainsDecideRule -- it just auto-truncates the
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; deduced prefix even more, so that anything &quot;within the same domain&quot;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; (including subdomains and, for &quot;www.&quot;, sibling domains) is accepted.
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; For example, if your seed is:
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; http://www.example.com/images/index.html
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; ...then the usual convert-to-SURT-prefix procedure results in...
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; http://(com,example,www,)/images/
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; If OnHostsDecideRule is used, that gets further truncated to...
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; http://(com,example,www,)/
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; ...which allows all URLs on that same exact host to be matched. If
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; OnDomainsDecideRule is used, that gets further truncated to...
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; http://(com,example,
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; ...so everything on &#39;example.com&#39; domain and subdomains is matched.
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; (&#39;www,)/&#39; is special-case stripped; for any other subdomains only the
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; &#39;)/&#39; would be stripped.
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; I still don&#39;t understand what the property name is for defining URI&#39;s to accept (if I want to do it inline instead of in a file). I haven&#39;t been able to find a proper documentation of the properties available. Is there none, do I have to go looking in the source to figure it out?
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; If it&#39;s not yet documented in the User Guide, the source or hints in the
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; example configuration files are the only other documentation.
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; SurtPrefixedDecideRule and its subclasses only accept prefixes from your
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; seeds, or another &#39;surtsSourceFile&#39;. They don&#39;t accept an inline list of
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; prefixes. (They theoretically could but haven&#39;t yet been set up that way.)
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; This is the definition in the default config:
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.surt.SurtPrefixedDecideRule&quot;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;!--
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;     &lt;property name=&quot;seedsAsSurtPrefixes&quot; value=&quot;true&quot; /&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; --&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;!--&lt;property name=&quot;alsoCheckVia&quot; value=&quot;true&quot; /&gt;    --&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;!--&lt;property name=&quot;surtsSourceFile&quot; value=&quot;&quot; /&gt;    --&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;!--
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;     &lt;property name=&quot;surtsDumpFile&quot; value=&quot;surts.dump&quot; /&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; --&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;/bean&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; seedsAsSurtPrefixes in commented out, but does it still default to true? All I want to do now is limit the crawl to a specific domain. So it feels like overkill to have a file just to store one line with www.xxx.yyy in.
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; As noted atop the example/default configuration files:
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; &quot;  Commented-out beans and properties are provided as an example; values
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;       shown in comments reflect the actual defaults which are in effect
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;       without specification. (To change from the default behavior,
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;       uncomment AND alter the shown values.)   &quot;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; So you only need to uncomment and change the &#39;seedsAsSurtPrefixes&#39; line
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; if you want to change its value to false.
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Have you tried a crawl with the default scope to see what it does? If
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; your seed URL is &quot;http://www.example.com&quot; and you do a crawl with the
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; default settings, the crawl stays on &quot;http://www.example.com&quot; URLs,
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; except where it seems offsite URLs are necessary to render pages (as
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; with IMGs, SCRIPTs, FRAMEs, and Javascript-mentioned URLs).
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; That&#39;s the automatic effect of the SurtPrefixedDecideRule being in the
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; default scope with &#39;seedsAsSurtPrefixes&#39; being true.
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Only if you need to tweak that usual behavior do you need to swap in
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; different rule classes or change properties. And even there, you can
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; instead put other directives into the &#39;seeds&#39; text that the
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; SurtPrefixedDecideRule will interpret. For example, lines that begin &quot;+&quot;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; are treated as SURT hints rather than actual seeds. So if your seeds
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; text (inline or from a file) is...
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; #=======
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; http://www.example.com/images/index.html
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; +http://(com,example,
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; #=======
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; ...then crawling starts on that one seed, but scoping accepts all URLs
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; matched by the prefix&lt;http://(com,example,&gt;   -- that is, everything on
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; example.com and any subdomains.
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; If SurtPrefixedDecideRule can&#39;t be used to keep the crawl within one domain I guess I should use OnDomainsDecideRule. But I have the same question there, what&#39;s the property name I need to use to define the URI/SURT? If there is no inline way of doing this should I use &quot;surtsSourceFile&quot; for OnDomainsDecideRule as well?
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; As noted above, I doubt your scenario requires using alternate rule
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; classes or a &#39;surtsSourceFile&#39; at all. But if it did, you supply a
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; filesystem path in the &#39;surtsSourceFile&#39; property, which may be absolute
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; or relative to the job directory (the directory containing the &#39;.cxml&#39;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; file).
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Thanks for your help!
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; You&#39;re welcome, hope this helps!
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; - Gordon @ IA
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; --- In archive-crawler@yahoogroups.com, Gordon Mohr&lt;gojomo@&gt;    wrote:
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; On 4/21/10 7:34 AM, Jens Bengtsson wrote:
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Hi!
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; I want to specify an OnHostsDecideRule and the Crawl Scope documentation says:
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; &quot;This DecideRule applies the configured decision to any URI that is in one of the hosts of the configured set.&quot;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; How do I define the configured set?
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; What do I need besides the following?
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.surt.OnHostsDecideRule&quot;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;               &lt;property name=&quot;decision&quot; value=&quot;ACCEPT&quot;/&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;      &lt;/bean&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; OnHostsDecideRule is a specialization of SurtPrefixedDecideRule.
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Both these rules can build their internal list of configured prefixes
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; (against which URIs are tested) from one or both of:
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; (1) the crawl&#39;s configured seeds -- if setting property
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; seedsAsSurtPrefixes is true (which is the default)
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; (2) a supplied file of URIs or prefixes, one to a line, via the
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; &#39;surtsSourceFile&#39; setting property (a path to the file to use)
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; In addition to the usual ways that desired prefixes are deduced from
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; URIs but SurtPrefixedDecideRule, for OnHostsDecideRule all prefixes are
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; truncated to the host component.
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; For example, SurtPrefixedDecideRule will turn the URI
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;http://example.com/images/&gt;    into the implied SURT prefix
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;http://(com,example,)/images/&gt;. OnHostsDecideRule will further truncate
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; that prefix to&lt;http://(com,example,)/&gt;, causing more URIs to be matched.
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Everything OnHostsDecideRule can do, SurtPrefixedDecideRule can do, too
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; -- if SurtPrefixedDecideRule is supplied with URIs/prefixes already
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; limited to the host-portion. For that reason, OnHostsDecideRule might be
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; discouraged/deprecated/deleted someday, so that there aren&#39;t redundant
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; ways to achieve the same effect.
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; - Gordon @ IA
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
